properties.areaDesc: South Central Elko County; Southern Lander County and Southern Eureka County; White Pine County; Northeastern Nye County; Ruby Mountains and East Humboldt Range; Southeastern Elko County
properties.headline: Wind Advisory issued February 1 at 2:57PM PST until February 3 at 7:00PM PST by NWS Elko NV
properties.description:
* WHAT...Post-cold front northwest winds of 25 to 35 mph with
gusts up to 55 mph expected. Isolated stronger wind gusts over
60 mph possible in higher terrain and areas of favorable
downslope winds including Ruby and Clover Valleys and in the
vicinity of Wendover.

* WHERE...Southeastern Elko County, Ruby Mountains/East Humboldt
Range, White Pine County, Southern Lander County and Southern
Eureka County, South Central Elko County and Northeastern Nye
County.

* WHEN...From 4 AM to 7 PM PST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Gusty winds will make driving high profile vehicles
difficult and could blow around unsecured objects as well as
cause a few power outages mainly in rural areas
properties.instruction:
Use extra caution when driving, especially if operating a high
profile vehicle. Secure outdoor objects.

NWSheadline: WIND ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 4 AM TO 7 PM PST MONDAY
